<subSubSection pageId="15" pageNumber="16" type="species composition">
<paragraph pageId="15" pageNumber="16">Species composition.</paragraph>
<paragraph pageId="15" pageNumber="16">
There are at least 14 valid species in the Western Palearctic: 
<taxonomicName authority="" authorityName="" class="Insecta" family="Megachilidae" genus="Carduoideae" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Carduoideae (Megachile) alpicola" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="15" pageNumber="16" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="alpicola" subGenus="Megachile">Megachile alpicola</taxonomicName>
Alfken, 1924, 
<taxonomicName authority="" authorityName="" class="Insecta" family="Megachilidae" genus="Carduoideae" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Carduoideae (M.) armenia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="15" pageNumber="16" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="armenia" subGenus="M.">M. armenia</taxonomicName>
, 
<taxonomicName authority="" authorityName="" class="Insecta" family="Megachilidae" genus="Carduoideae" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Carduoideae (M.) bombycina" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="15" pageNumber="16" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="bombycina" subGenus="M.">M. bombycina</taxonomicName>
, 
<taxonomicName authority="" authorityName="" class="Insecta" family="Megachilidae" genus="Carduoideae" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Carduoideae (M.) calloleuca" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="15" pageNumber="16" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="calloleuca" subGenus="M.">M. calloleuca</taxonomicName>
, 
<taxonomicName authority="" authorityName="" class="Insecta" family="Megachilidae" genus="Carduoideae" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Carduoideae (M.) centuncularis" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="15" pageNumber="16" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="centuncularis" subGenus="M.">M. centuncularis</taxonomicName>
(Linnaeus, 1758), 
<taxonomicName authority="" authorityName="" class="Insecta" family="Megachilidae" genus="Carduoideae" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Carduoideae (M.) genalis" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="15" pageNumber="16" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="genalis" subGenus="M.">M. genalis</taxonomicName>
, 
<taxonomicName authority="" authorityName="" class="Insecta" family="Megachilidae" genus="Carduoideae" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Carduoideae (M.) lapponica" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="15" pageNumber="16" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="lapponica" subGenus="M.">M. lapponica</taxonomicName>
, 
<taxonomicName authority="" authorityName="" class="Insecta" family="Megachilidae" genus="Carduoideae" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Carduoideae (M.) ligniseca" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="15" pageNumber="16" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="ligniseca" subGenus="M.">M. ligniseca</taxonomicName>
, 
<taxonomicName authority="" authorityName="" class="Insecta" family="Megachilidae" genus="Carduoideae" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Carduoideae (M.) melanopyga" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="15" pageNumber="16" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="melanopyga" subGenus="M.">M. melanopyga</taxonomicName>
, 
<taxonomicName authority="" authorityName="" class="Insecta" family="Megachilidae" genus="Carduoideae" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Carduoideae (M.) melanota" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="15" pageNumber="16" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="melanota" subGenus="M.">M. melanota</taxonomicName>
<normalizedToken originalValue="Pérez">Perez</normalizedToken>
, 1895, 
<taxonomicName authority="" authorityName="" class="Insecta" family="Megachilidae" genus="Carduoideae" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Carduoideae (M.) octosignata" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="15" pageNumber="16" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="octosignata" subGenus="M.">M. octosignata</taxonomicName>
Nylander, 1852, 
<taxonomicName authority="" authorityName="" class="Insecta" family="Megachilidae" genus="Carduoideae" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Carduoideae (M.) pilicrus" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="15" pageNumber="16" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="pilicrus" subGenus="M.">M. pilicrus</taxonomicName>
, 
<taxonomicName authority="" authorityName="" class="Insecta" family="Megachilidae" genus="Carduoideae" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Carduoideae (M.) pyrenaea" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="15" pageNumber="16" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="pyrenaea" subGenus="M.">M. pyrenaea</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName authority="" authorityName="" class="Insecta" family="Megachilidae" genus="Carduoideae" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Carduoideae (M.) versicolor" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="15" pageNumber="16" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="versicolor" subGenus="M.">M. versicolor</taxonomicName>
. I have not been able to locate the type of 
<taxonomicName authority="" authorityName="" class="Insecta" family="Megachilidae" genus="Carduoideae" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Carduoideae (M.) dacica" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="15" pageNumber="16" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="dacica" subGenus="M.">M. dacica</taxonomicName>
<normalizedToken originalValue="Mocsáry">Mocsary</normalizedToken>
, 1879; 
<bibRefCitation author="Schwarz, M" journalOrPublisher="Entomofauna Supplement 8, Ansfelden" pageId="24" pageNumber="25" title="Katalog der Bienen Oesterreichs, Deutschlands und der Schweiz (Hymenoptera, Apidae)." year="1996">Schwarz et al. (1996)</bibRefCitation>
and 
<bibRefCitation author="Westrich, P" journalOrPublisher="Eucera" pageId="25" pageNumber="26" pagination="3 - 18" title="Bienen (Hymenoptera, Apidae) als Bluetenbesucher von Odontitesviscosus und Odontitesluteus (Scrophulariaceae)." url="http://www.wildbienen.info/downloads/eucera-6–2011.pdf" volume="6" year="2011">Westrich (2011)</bibRefCitation>
recognized this species as valid; in contrast, according to identified material in his collection (OLML), B. 
<normalizedToken originalValue="Tkalců">Tkalcu</normalizedToken>
considered 
<taxonomicName authority="" authorityName="" class="Insecta" family="Megachilidae" genus="Carduoideae" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Carduoideae dacica" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="15" pageNumber="16" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="dacica">dacica</taxonomicName>
as a valid subspecies of 
<taxonomicName authority="" authorityName="" class="Insecta" family="Megachilidae" genus="Carduoideae" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Carduoideae (M.) lapponica" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="15" pageNumber="16" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="lapponica" subGenus="M.">M. lapponica</taxonomicName>
. The status of 
<taxonomicName authority="" authorityName="" class="Insecta" family="Megachilidae" genus="Carduoideae" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Carduoideae (M.) melanota" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="15" pageNumber="16" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="melanota" subGenus="M.">M. melanota</taxonomicName>
is unclear, as it may represent a dark color form of 
<taxonomicName authority="" authorityName="" class="Insecta" family="Megachilidae" genus="Carduoideae" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Carduoideae (M.) octosignata" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="15" pageNumber="16" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="octosignata" subGenus="M.">M. octosignata</taxonomicName>
.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="15" pageNumber="16" type="biology_ecology">
<paragraph pageId="15" pageNumber="16">Biology.</paragraph>
<paragraph pageId="15" pageNumber="16">
All species are leafcutters and build brood cells made of leaf fragments (e.g. 
<bibRefCitation author="Malysheva, MS" journalOrPublisher="Entomological review" pageId="22" pageNumber="23" pagination="268 - 276" title="Leaf-cutting bees of the genus Megachile Latr. (Hymenoptera, Megachilidae) injurious to young forest stands and shelter belts in the USSR." volume="37" year="1958">Malysheva 1958</bibRefCitation>
, 
<bibRefCitation author="Westrich, P" journalOrPublisher="Ulmer, Stuttgart" pageId="25" pageNumber="26" title="Die Wildbienen Baden-Wuerttembergs." year="1989">Westrich 1989</bibRefCitation>
, 
<bibRefCitation author="Ruhnke, H" journalOrPublisher="Mitteilungen der Deutschen Gesellschaft fuer Allgemeine und Angewandte Entomologie" pageId="24" pageNumber="25" pagination="513 - 516" title="Zur Nistbiologie der Megachilegenalis Mor (Hymenoptera: Apidae)." volume="12" year="2000">Ruhnke 2000</bibRefCitation>
); no Palearctic species appears to use petals as documented in the Nearctic 
<taxonomicName authority="" authorityName="" class="Insecta" family="Megachilidae" genus="Carduoideae" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Carduoideae (Megachile) montivaga" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="15" pageNumber="16" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="montivaga" subGenus="Megachile">Megachile montivaga</taxonomicName>
(Michener, 2007, and references therein; 
<bibRefCitation author="Orr, MC" journalOrPublisher="Journal of Melittology" pageId="23" pageNumber="24" pagination="1 - 6" title="Megachile (Megachile) montivaga (Hymenoptera: Megachilidae) nesting in live thistle (Asteraceae: Cirsium)." url="https://doi.org/10.17161/jom.v0i48.4847" volume="48" year="2015">Orr et al. 2015</bibRefCitation>
). The nests are mostly located in existing, above-ground cavities; some species such as 
<taxonomicName authority="" authorityName="" class="Insecta" family="Megachilidae" genus="Carduoideae" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Carduoideae (M.) centuncularis" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="15" pageNumber="16" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="centuncularis" subGenus="M.">M. centuncularis</taxonomicName>
are flexible and nest both in above-ground cavities and in the soil (
<bibRefCitation author="Westrich, P" journalOrPublisher="Ulmer, Stuttgart" pageId="25" pageNumber="26" title="Die Wildbienen Baden-Wuerttembergs." year="1989">Westrich 1989</bibRefCitation>
, and references therein). Nests of 
<taxonomicName authority="" authorityName="" class="Insecta" family="Megachilidae" genus="Carduoideae" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Carduoideae (M.) pyrenaea" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="15" pageNumber="16" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="pyrenaea" subGenus="M.">M. pyrenaea</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName authority="" authorityName="" class="Insecta" family="Megachilidae" genus="Carduoideae" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Carduoideae (M.) octosignata" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="15" pageNumber="16" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="octosignata" subGenus="M.">M. octosignata</taxonomicName>
are placed under stones or in the soil (
<bibRefCitation author="Ferton, C" journalOrPublisher="Annales de la Societe Entomologique de France" pageId="21" pageNumber="22" pagination="401 - 422" title="Notes detachees sur l'instinct des hymenopteres melliferes et ravisseurs (5 eme serie) avec la description d'une espece nouvelle." volume="78" year="1909">Ferton 1909</bibRefCitation>
, 
<bibRefCitation author="Grandi, G" journalOrPublisher="Bollettino dell'Istituto di Entomologia dell'Universita di Bologna" pageId="22" pageNumber="23" title="Studi di un entomologo sugli imenotteri superiori" volume="25" year="1961">Grandi 1961</bibRefCitation>
, 
<bibRefCitation author="Westrich, P" journalOrPublisher="Ulmer, Stuttgart" pageId="25" pageNumber="26" title="Die Wildbienen Baden-Wuerttembergs." year="1989">Westrich 1989</bibRefCitation>
), and a nest of 
<taxonomicName authority="" authorityName="" class="Insecta" family="Megachilidae" genus="Carduoideae" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Carduoideae (M.) melanopyga" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="15" pageNumber="16" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="melanopyga" subGenus="M.">M. melanopyga</taxonomicName>
was found &quot;loose in the grass&quot; (
<bibRefCitation author="Friese, H" journalOrPublisher="Friedlaender, Berlin" pageId="22" pageNumber="23" title="Die Bienen Europa's (Apidae europaeae). Theil V. Solitaere Apiden: Genus Lithurgus. Genus Megachile (Chalicodoma)." year="1898">Friese 1898</bibRefCitation>
). 
<taxonomicName authority="" authorityName="" class="Insecta" family="Megachilidae" genus="Carduoideae" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Carduoideae (M.) genalis" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="15" pageNumber="16" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="genalis" subGenus="M.">M. genalis</taxonomicName>
exclusively nests in standing stems, favoring fresh stems, thus from plants of the same year; the female digs an opening and places the brood cells vertically above or below the entrance (
<bibRefCitation author="Ruhnke, H" journalOrPublisher="Mitteilungen der Deutschen Gesellschaft fuer Allgemeine und Angewandte Entomologie" pageId="24" pageNumber="25" pagination="513 - 516" title="Zur Nistbiologie der Megachilegenalis Mor (Hymenoptera: Apidae)." volume="12" year="2000">Ruhnke 2000</bibRefCitation>
, and references therein). According to a brief account by 
<bibRefCitation author="Friese, H" journalOrPublisher="Friedlaender, Berlin" pageId="22" pageNumber="23" title="Die Bienen Europa's (Apidae europaeae). Theil V. Solitaere Apiden: Genus Lithurgus. Genus Megachile (Chalicodoma)." year="1898">Friese (1898)</bibRefCitation>
, 
<taxonomicName authority="" authorityName="" class="Insecta" family="Megachilidae" genus="Carduoideae" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Carduoideae (M.) pilicrus" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="15" pageNumber="16" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="pilicrus" subGenus="M.">M. pilicrus</taxonomicName>
nests in dry stems of thistles.
</paragraph>
<paragraph pageId="15" pageNumber="16">
Most species of the subgenus 
<taxonomicName authority="" authorityName="" class="Insecta" family="Megachilidae" genus="Carduoideae" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Carduoideae (Megachile)" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="15" pageNumber="16" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="subGenus" subGenus="Megachile">Megachile</taxonomicName>
are polylectic, often with a preference for 
<taxonomicName authority="" authorityName="" class="Insecta" family="Fabaceae" genus="Carduoideae" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Carduoideae" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="15" pageNumber="16" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="family">Fabaceae</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName authority="" authorityName="" class="Insecta" family="Asteraceae" genus="Carduoideae" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Carduoideae" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="15" pageNumber="16" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="family">Asteraceae</taxonomicName>
(
<bibRefCitation author="Westrich, P" journalOrPublisher="Ulmer, Stuttgart" pageId="25" pageNumber="26" title="Die Wildbienen Baden-Wuerttembergs." year="1989">Westrich 1989</bibRefCitation>
). 
<taxonomicName authority="" authorityName="" class="Insecta" family="Megachilidae" genus="Carduoideae" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Carduoideae (Megachile) lapponica" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="15" pageNumber="16" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="lapponica" subGenus="Megachile">Megachile lapponica</taxonomicName>
is an oligolege on 
<taxonomicName class="Magnoliopsida" family="Onagraceae" genus="Epilobium" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="Epilobium" order="Myrtales" pageId="15" pageNumber="16" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="genus">Epilobium</taxonomicName>
(
<bibRefCitation author="Westrich, P" journalOrPublisher="Ulmer, Stuttgart" pageId="25" pageNumber="26" title="Die Wildbienen Baden-Wuerttembergs." year="1989">Westrich 1989</bibRefCitation>
, 
<bibRefCitation author="Kuehn, J" journalOrPublisher="Mitteilungen der Deutschen Gesellschaft fuer Allgemeine und Angewandte Entomologie" pageId="22" pageNumber="23" pagination="389 - 392" title="Ressourcenaufteilung zwischen der oligolektischen Blattschneiderbiene Megachilelapponica L. (Hymenoptera, Apiformes) und anderen Bluetenbesuchern am schmalblaettrigen Weidenroeschen (Epilobiumangustifolium, Onagraceae)." volume="15" year="2006">
<normalizedToken originalValue="Kühn">Kuehn</normalizedToken>
et al. 2006
</bibRefCitation>
), while 
<taxonomicName authority="" authorityName="" class="Insecta" family="Megachilidae" genus="Carduoideae" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Carduoideae (M.) genalis" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="15" pageNumber="16" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="genalis" subGenus="M.">M. genalis</taxonomicName>
is possibly oligolectic on 
<taxonomicName authority="" authorityName="" class="Insecta" family="Asteraceae" genus="Carduoideae" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Carduoideae" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="15" pageNumber="16" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="family">Asteraceae</taxonomicName>
(
<bibRefCitation author="Westrich, P" journalOrPublisher="Ulmer, Stuttgart" pageId="25" pageNumber="26" title="Die Wildbienen Baden-Wuerttembergs." year="1989">Westrich 1989</bibRefCitation>
); 
<taxonomicName authority="" authorityName="" class="Insecta" family="Megachilidae" genus="Carduoideae" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Carduoideae (M.) pilicrus" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="15" pageNumber="16" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="pilicrus" subGenus="M.">M. pilicrus</taxonomicName>
is oligolectic on 
<taxonomicName authority="" authorityName="" class="Insecta" family="Megachilidae" genus="Carduoideae" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Carduoideae" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="15" pageNumber="16" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="subfamily" subfamily="Carduoideae">Carduoideae</taxonomicName>
and its hind trochanter and femur are covered by modified, stiff hairs, as observed in some 
<taxonomicName authority="" authorityName="" class="Insecta" family="Megachilidae" genus="Carduoideae" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Carduoideae (Eutricharaea)" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="15" pageNumber="16" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="subGenus" subGenus="Eutricharaea">Eutricharaea</taxonomicName>
species specialized on these plants (
<bibRefCitation author="Mueller, A" journalOrPublisher="Apidologie" pageId="23" pageNumber="24" pagination="329 - 337" title="A specialized pollen-harvesting device in western palaearctic bees of the genus Megachile (Hymenoptera, Apoidea, Megachilidae)." url="https://doi.org/10.1051/apido:2004020" volume="35" year="2004">
<normalizedToken originalValue="Müller">Mueller</normalizedToken>
and Bansac 2004
</bibRefCitation>
).
</paragraph>
